Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper heavily relies on reinforcement learning to optimize the prediction capacity of the models generated by the multi-agent meta-modeling game. 
2. cs.LG - The use of deep reinforcement learning to automatically search for the optimal choices in a decision tree search falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.SI - The paper discusses the use of a multi-agent system to generate data, knowledge, and models, which falls under the category of social intelligence. 
4. cs.CE - The paper discusses the use of virtual experiments (e.g. molecular dynamics, discrete element simulations) to generate data, which falls under the category of computational engineering. 
5. cs.SY - The paper discusses the use of a directed multigraph to evaluate all the modeling options, which falls under the category of systems and control.
